'''Yanto Tanoto''' (Chinese name: '''Chen Jianghai''', 15 April 1955 - 26 September 1997) was a Singaporean businessman. He was born in [[Medan]], Indonesia. He served as the CEO of Singapore's Golden Eagle Group as well as the CEO of [[Asia Pacific Resources International Holdings]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/default.aspx?pageid=438&n=indonesian-plane-crashes-in-smog-area-234-die-1997-09-27|title=Indonesian plane crashes in smog area, 234 die|date=27 September 1997|access-date=27 March 2013}}</ref> In 1997, he was killed in the crash of [[Garuda Indonesia Flight 152]]. He is the younger brother of Indonesia's richest person, [[Sukanto Tanoto]].<ref name="forbes2008">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2008/03/07/five-indonesians-039forbes039-rich-list.html|title=Five Indonesians on 'Forbes' rich list|date=2008-03-08|publisher=The Jakarta Post|access-date=2008-03-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://whatisgenius.blogspot.tw/2011/04/billionaire-with-worst-environmental.html|title=What is Genius|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130419161202/http://whatisgenius.blogspot.tw/2011/04/billionaire-with-worst-environmental.html|archive-date=19 April 2013|dead-url=yes|access-date=27 March 2013}}</ref>

